Conflict in Libya (File, AFP). Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Benghazi - Libyan officials say several rockets fired from areas held by the Islamic State group have landed in Benghazi's city center, killing three civilians and wounding more than a dozen.Libyan National Army spokesperson Brigadier General Ahmed Mosmari says the rockets hit near a gas station in a crowded street of the Sidi Hussien area on Tuesday. He says the wounded were brought to Jala Hospital.The area is located a few kilometers (miles) from the front lines, where the remnants of ISIS fighters and other Islamic militias control coastal territory.The army, led by Field Marshal Khalifa Hifter, has issued a statement criminalizing the act and condemning those who target civilians. The army is leading the fight against IS in Libya's east.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.